last_episode_to_air.name: Outer Space
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Looney Builders build Marvin the Martian and his Martian crew a space station. Marvin soon becomes overwhelmed by his Martian crew's antics and lack of personal space.

name: Bugs Bunny Builders
overview: At ACME Construction Company, Bugs Bunny and Lola Bunny manage an inept crew of builders. By working together as a team, Daffy Duck, Porky Pig, Tweety, and others use their tools and wild vehicles to pull off some of the looniest construction jobs ever.

episodes.name: Splash Zone
episodes.overview: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg’s waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

episodes.name: Ice Creamed
episodes.overview: It’s Taz’s birthday, so The Looney Builders build him a huge ice cream sundae. Porky worries about making a mistake and delays the build causing the ice cream to start to melt.

episodes.name: Race Track Race
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders race against the clock to build Cecil Turtle a new racetrack. Daffy gets caught up in his own desire to race and changes part of the build.

episodes.name: Dino Fright
episodes.overview: George P. Mandrake hires The Looney Builders to build a T. Rex fossil. It’s Tweety’s job to place the bones with his crane, but his fear of the big dino affects his ability to get the job done.

episodes.name: Snow Cap
episodes.overview: Pauleen Penguin hires The Looney Builders to build her a home in Looneyburg. Lola soon discovers they got the design wrong and the crew has to make adjustments.

episodes.name: Tweety-Go-Round
episodes.overview: Tweety leads The Looney Builders in building a new merry-go-round at the park for the kids. His crane breaks down and his small size affects his ability to contribute to the build.

guest_stars.character: Looney Kangaroo Kid / Looney Cat Kid (voice)
guest_stars.name: Debi Derryberry

episodes.name: Smash House
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders learn that Taz accidentally destroyed his house, so they set out to build him a new one that’s smash-proof.

episodes.name: Play Day
episodes.overview: When the Looney Builders build themselves a playground, Daffy gets so excited about his section that he takes all the supplies for himself.

episodes.name: Rock On
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders are hired by Mac and Tosh Gopher to build them a home underground. Daffy can’t remove rocks from the area fast enough and fails to ask for help.

episodes.name: Buzz In
episodes.overview: Bizzy Buzzard’s mom hires The Looney Builders to build her family a new nest. Bizzy wants to help but keeps getting in the way creating all sorts of problems for the crew.

episodes.name: Stories
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders are hired by Hoots Talon to expand and paint the old library. They enlist master painter Sylvester who faces his fear of heights with his build buddy, Tweety.

episodes.name: Cheesy Peasy
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders are hired by the Mouse Sisters to build a bridge over a mac and cheese spill. Lola turns the job into a game which results in the crew losing sight of the bigger goal.

episodes.name: Looney Science
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders build a science museum in the desert where Wile E. Coyote becomes distracted by the Road Runner.

episodes.name: Big Feet
episodes.overview: Mayor Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a water wheel in the forest where Porky worries about a mythical creature named "Big Feet."

episodes.name: Squirreled Away
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders build Tibs Squirrel a closet in his tree, but it won't fit all of Tibs' stuff and he doesn't want to get rid of anything.

episodes.name: Beach Battle
episodes.overview: When The Looney Builders enter a sandcastle building contest, Tweety sees the competition and loses confidence in his idea.

episodes.name: Game Time
episodes.overview: Chef Hector hires The Looney Builders to build him a burger restaurant, but Daffy is so focused on beating his handheld game that he causes major setbacks.

episodes.name: Soup Up
episodes.overview: As The Looney Builders help Petunia build a greenhouse, she can't wait for the veggies to grow and does everything she can to speed up the process.

episodes.name: Looneyburg Lights
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders prepare to host a big holiday lights festival in Looneyburg Park when an unexpected snowstorm prevents Looneyburgers from attending.

episodes.name: Blast Off
episodes.overview: When Marvin the Martian crash lands in Looneyburg, he's in a hurry to leave and hires The Looney Builders to build him a spaceship.

episodes.name: K-9: Space Puppy
episodes.overview: Marvin the Martian hires The Looney Builders to build a doghouse on Mars for his puppy, K-9. Daffy soon bonds with K-9 and comes up with a plan to prolong their playtime.

episodes.name: Cousin Billy
episodes.overview: When Daffy's cool cousin Billy hires The Looney Builders to build her an art studio, Daffy tries to show off to prove how cool he is.

episodes.name: Cheddar Days
episodes.overview: The Mouse Sisters hire The Looney Builders to build a cheese café featuring a mural by Sylvester who is having a bad day.

episodes.name: Taz Recycle
episodes.overview: When The Looney Builders build Taz a wrecking ball vehicle, he struggles to learn how to operate it.

episodes.name: Sea School
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders face underwater challenges as they build a sea school for Moxie Manatee.

episodes.name: Underwater Star
episodes.overview: Moxie Manatee hires The Looney Builders to build an obstacle course for the Sandy Shells Preschool Games, but Lola isn't listening to her crew.

episodes.name: Party Boat
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders build a party boat for Mac and Tosh when Tweety accidentally makes a mistake but doesn't ask for help.

episodes.name: Mail Whale
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders try to help Winston Whale by building him a mail truck, but Winston is used to working alone.

episodes.name: Bright Light
episodes.overview: When Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a lighthouse for Looneyburg, Lola's tablet breaks and she must rely on herself.

episodes.name: Mini Golf
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders redesign the final hole of ACME Acres Mini Golf Course, and Porky is determined to get it just right for the kids.

episodes.name: Goofballs
episodes.overview: The Beaver Brothers hire The Looney Builders to build them a log cabin, but soon sidetrack the job by goofing around too much.

episodes.name: Skate Park
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders build a skate park for the kids, but it soon interferes with Hoots Talon and his friends' activities.

episodes.name: Batty Kathy
episodes.overview: As The Looney Builders build Kathy Bat an upside-down radio station, Porky has concerns but doesn't speak up.

episodes.name: Honey Bunny
episodes.overview: Queen Beatrice hires The Looney Builders to build a workshop in her beehive where there is one rule the crew has trouble following.

episodes.name: Castle Hassle
episodes.overview: Prince Lionel of England hires The Looney Builders to build him a party room for his birthday, then proceeds to boss the crew around.

episodes.name: Catwalk
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders are hired by Penelope Pussycat to build a fashion runway in France where they are encouraged to make their design bigger and more fun.

episodes.name: Dim Sum
episodes.overview: Chef Poyung Panda hires The Looney Builders to build her a Dim Sum bus in China. The crew faces a major setback and Bugs worries about letting down his favorite chef.

episodes.name: Crane Game
episodes.overview: As The Looney Builders build a giant claw game for Chibi Critter's arcade in Japan, they discover the claw part is broken.

episodes.name: Speedy
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders rush to build a soccer stadium in Mexico for their fast customer, Speedy Gonzalez.

episodes.name: The Easter Bunnies
episodes.overview: The Easter Bunny is sick, so she hires The Looney Builders to take over the festivities and ensure Looneyburg has a great Easter.

episodes.name: Junior
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders are hired by Ma and Pa Bear to build a bedroom for their son, Junior, whose excitement causes setbacks.

episodes.name: Looney Moon
episodes.overview: When The Looney Builders help Wile E. Coyote build a telescope to view the Looney Moon, Tweety must face his fear of the dark.

episodes.name: Glamp Out
episodes.overview: Gossamer invites The Looney Builders on a camping trip. They plan to build a simple campsite until Daffy insists they go "glamping" instead.

episodes.name: Outer Space
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders build Marvin the Martian and his Martian crew a space station. Marvin soon becomes overwhelmed by his Martian crew's antics and lack of personal space.

episodes.name: The Great Flying Flea
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders discover Zippy, an acrobatic flea, living on Sylvester's back. They build Zippy a flea circus to try and convince him to relocate.

episodes.name: The Snuffles
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders are hired to build an outdoor movie theater in the park. Lola is sick, but she doesn't want to admit it.

episodes.name: Rainy Day
episodes.overview: When it starts to rain outside, Porky hopes to show The Looney Builders that they can still have fun inside by building a fort.

episodes.name: Bugs and the Beanstalk
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders build a castle for Elmer the Giant. They admire his toys and use them without his permission.

episodes.name: Looney Games
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders are hired by Mayor Leghorn to build the venue for the Looney Games. They soon become overwhelmed by the job and must ask for help.

episodes.name: Jazz Hooves
episodes.overview: Fosse Ferret hires The Looney Builders to build a stage for the kids’ dance recital. Eggbert has stage fright.

episodes.name: Roller Disco
episodes.overview: Pete Puma hires The Looney Builders to build a roller disco for Looneyburg. Lola is new to roller skating but doesn’t want to practice.

episodes.name: Grandpa Oink
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders are hired by Petunia’s Grandpa Oink to upgrade his farm.

episodes.name: Hare Ball
episodes.overview: Marvin the Martian hires The Looney Builders to build an outer space ball court on Mars. Bugs is a big fan of the sport.

episodes.name: Squeaky Clean
episodes.overview: The Looney Builders build their headquarters a car wash. Daffy doesn’t want to wash Dumpy and goes to extreme lengths to keep him dirty.
